title: Object incompatibility
body:
In R 3.4.0, "err.fun" yields an error because nd[, response] is a data
frame and the operation “obs - pred” cannot be computed.
Additionally, R 3.4.0 cannot call detectCores()  we should use parallel::detectCores()

title: sperrorest v1.0.0
body:
* fix `importance = TRUE` in `sperrorest()` and `parsperrorest()` fixes #15 

* remove `notify` package integration :( -> caused trouble on win-builder when running tests

* replace `snow` package with `parallel` and change cluster type from `"SOCK"` to `"PSOCK"` fixes #24 

* fix .bib problem of vignette -> removed .bib entry from `.Rbuildignore`

* DONTRUN tests in`sperrorest()` and `parsperrorest()` due to runtime > 5s

* use `apalike` citation style instead of modified app

* increase test-coverage #14
